ompany, Red Gate Shadow Theatre, was lauded by theatre and art critics and even performed at Franklin Roosevelt's White House. Grant Hayter-Menzies traces Benton's performance history and her efforts to preserve shadow theatre as a global cultural treasure by drawing on her unpublished writings, the recollections of her colleagues, the testimonies of shadow masters who survived China's Cultural Revolution, as well as young innovators who have carried on Benton's pioneering work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPerformance artxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aPerformance artzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPerformance artistsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aPerformance artistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPuppet theaterxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aPuppet theaterzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPuppeteersxBiographyxUnited States. 0aPuppeteerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aShadow puppetsxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aShadow puppetszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aShadow showsxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aShadow showszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen performance artistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aWomen puppeteerszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Women.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358909440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773589094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773589094/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles